It does catch one thing that my usual testing doesn't: trailing commas.  I am in the habit of defining maps like this:<p><pre><code>   var foo = {
       foo: "bar",
       bar: "baz",
   };
</code></pre>
This works in Firefox, but not in IE.  Arghhh!<p>Perhaps I should do it Haskell-style:<p><pre><code>    var foo = { foo: "bar"
              , bar: "baz"
              };
</code></pre>
I find that to be pretty ugly, though, and think it's easier to just omit the trailing comma.  Reluctantly.
